<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6894&amp;p=66640#p66640"><![CDATA[
Exactly, it is either a game or a tech demo, and not merely an engine.  Even a level of null data is providing something for the engine to work with.<br /><br />One could argue that a screen with a single red square that you can move around is a sandbox game.  Set your own goals!  See how fast you can move it side to side!  See if you can get the square to sit in the exact corner of the screen!<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3438">UncleSporky</a> — Tue Aug 24, 2010 6:06 am</p><hr />
