<title type="html"><![CDATA[Where do you draw the line between an engine and a game?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6894&amp;p=66601#p66601"><![CDATA[
The engine is the code and the data that you can recycle into a new project, with which you can make another game.<br /><br />A game is just how you use the engine. <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_razz.gif" alt=":P" title="Razz" /><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=21">Drag</a> — Mon Aug 23, 2010 5:53 pm</p><hr />
